					  - By Mike Cherney
		  
An Australian regulator is suing Ford, saying it misled customers who complained about the dry-clutch PowerShift automatic transmission  by telling them they weren’t entitled to a refund or a replacement vehicle.


House passes bill hitting Russia with new sanctions
7:23 p.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Natalie Andrews
		  
In a rare, overwhelmingly bipartisan vote, the House on Tuesday passed new sanctions that would punish Russia, after the U.S. intelligence community concluded that it had sought to interfere in the 2016 presidential election.


Former Trump campaign chief Manafort strikes deal to avoid public testimony
7:01 p.m. July 25, 2017
					  -  Byron Tau
		  
President Donald Trump’s former campaign chairman reached an agreement with Capitol Hill investigators Tuesday to avoid public testimony about Russian meddling in the 2016 presidential election, heading off the threat of being compelled to appear, according to a person familiar with the matter.


Obama-era rule that would have extended overtime pay to millions may get revised
1:55 p.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Eric Morath
		  
The Labor Department will begin the process reconsidering rules around when workers are eligible for overtime pay, potentially undoing one of the Obama administration’s major labor-policy changes.


Which state’s 529 plan is right for you?
1:12 p.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Chana R. Schoenberger
		  
In some ways, deciding which state’s plan is best for you is like picking mutual funds for a retirement account.


China prepares for a security crisis along 880-mile North Korea border
9:57 a.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Jeremy Page
		  
China has been bolstering defenses along its 880-mile frontier with North Korea and realigning forces in surrounding regions to prepare for a potential crisis across their border, including the possibility of a U.S. military strike.


YouTube and Hulu TV bundles will be rated like traditional networks by Nielsen
8:45 a.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Alexandra Bruell
		  
Nielsen said it has begun counting viewership on new streaming TV services offered by Hulu and YouTube toward the official ratings for shows, its latest step to modernize measurement standards as digital consumption increases.


Why some older investors might invest in a long-term time horizon
7:53 a.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Patrick Lach
		  
It’s important to realize that the investor’s lifespan and the time horizon of the portfolio are not one and the same.


Michael Kors buying shoe maker Jimmy Choo for $1.2 billion in all-cash deal
7:40 a.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Saabira Chaudhuri
		  
Michael Kors on Tuesday said it has agreed to acquire upscale shoemaker Jimmy Choo for £896 million ($1.17 billion), as it looks to offset slower growth in its core handbag business.


Barnes & Noble pressed by activist investor Sandell to sell itself
7:33 a.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By David Benoit and Jeffrey A. Trachtenberg
		  
Barnes & Noble is being pressured by activist investor Sandell Asset Management Corp. to sell itself.


SoftBank pursues multibillion-dollar stake in Uber
4:45 a.m. July 25, 2017
					  - By Greg Bensinger
		  
The Japanese tech giant SoftBank — a big investor in Asian ride-hailing companies Grab, Ola and Didi Chuxing — has approached Uber about taking a multibillion-dollar stake, people familiar with the matter said.


U.S. will go single-payer route on health care: Jimmy Carter
4:51 p.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By Louise Radnofsky
		  
Former President Jimmy Carter said he believed the U.S. would in time adopt a fully government-run health insurance system, or “Medicare for all,” in remarks ahead of his Sunday-school class here.


Wall Street trader makes $265 million bet on VIX surging by October
2:04 p.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By Gunjan Banerji
		  
One investor has bet on a powerful resurgence in market turbulence—a wager that could net a profit of about $265 million if Wall Street’s fear gauge more than doubles in the next three months.


Democrats’ ‘Better Deal’ agenda calls for cutting drug costs, boosting minimum wage
12:36 p.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By Natalie Andrews
		  
Democrats are launching a new policy agenda focused on the economy that seeks to bridge gaps with voters amid polls showing most Americans don’t know what the party stands for. 


BMW denies claims that German car makers may have operated a cartel
7:12 a.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By William Boston
		  
BMW says it did not cooperate with rivals to manipulate diesel engines for reducing nitrogen-oxide emissions, after  VW asks EU antitrust watchdogs to scrutinize decades of possible coordination efforts by the Germany’s main auto makers.


Jared Kushner denies collusion with Russians as he reveals he did meet with ambassador
6:53 a.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By Rebecca Ballhaus
		  
President Donald Trump’s son-in-law and senior White House adviser Jared Kushner releases details on his previously undisclosed meeting with Russian ambassador Sergei Kislyak at an event at Washington hotel.


Apple supplier Foxconn nearing decision about producing display panels in Wisconsin
6:25 a.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By Yoko Kubota
		  
Taiwan’s Foxconn Technology Group, which assembles Apple Inc.’s iPhones, is nearing a decision to invest in Wisconsin and could hold an event in Washington, D.C., as soon as this week to discuss U.S. investment plans, people familiar with the matter said.


KKR close to announcing deal for WebMD
2:03 a.m. July 24, 2017
					  - By Matt Jarzemsky
		  
The New York-based health-information provider could announce the deal as soon as Monday, the people said.


White House indicates support for Russia sanctions bill
4:35 p.m. July 23, 2017
					  - By Natalie Andrews
		  
The White House supports legislation that would punish Russia for its interference in the 2016 election, a spokeswoman said Sunday, despite its previous objection to measures restricting the president’s power to remove sanctions on Moscow.


Jordan Spieth wins British Open by three shots in dramatic comeback
2:43 p.m. July 23, 2017
					  - By Matthew Futterman
		  
Jordan Spieth won the British Open after a roller coaster final round.


Congress reaches deal on sweeping Russia sanctions bill
10:43 a.m. July 23, 2017
					  - By Natalie Andrews
		  
Congressional negotiators reached a deal late Friday to advance a bill that would punish Russia for its interference in the 2016 election and restrict the president’s power to remove sanctions on Moscow.


U.S. giving takeover bids by Chinese firms much tougher look
2:25 p.m. July 22, 2017
					  - By Kate O'Keeffe
		  
The U.S. is toughening scrutiny of Chinese deals, throwing number of high-profile takeover bids into question.









